<h3>My LG dryer in my CSUF area apartment shows d80 — the building replaced the machine but the code came back. Why?</h3>
<p>The problem is the building vent, not the machine. Shared duct infrastructure in CSUF-area apartment buildings accumulates lint from multiple units running heavily during the academic year. Replacing the individual machine doesn't clear the building duct. We clear the building vent system and replace the foil transition duct behind the stack — d80 goes away and stays away.</p>

<h3>My older Fullerton home has never had the dryer vent cleaned — how urgent is this?</h3>
<p>Very urgent for 1950s–1960s homes in Raymond Hills, Richman, and Maple Park. Original vent runs with 50–60 years of dry compacted lint are a fire hazard. We use extended two-pass cleaning and measure airflow before and after. Vent cleaning $150–200 prevents a $280–350 fuse failure. Code compliance check on 1950s installations.</p>

<h3>Can you repair all LG dryer models in Fullerton?</h3>
<p>Yes — DLGX, DLEX, and DLE series including gas and electric. DLGX models common in Sunny Hills and Rolling Hills hillside homes. Older DLE series in Raymond Hills and Richman 1950s–1960s housing. ThinQ-enabled models in Amerige Heights newer builds. Parts for all common Fullerton models on the truck.</p>

